Common Technical Problems and answers:


To help troubleshoot the game, Trade Wars sends error messages to standard
output.  You can capture output to a file and see what messages were sent
even if they weren't visible on the screen.  Just run the game like this:

At the command line:

  TW2002 > ERR.LOG

From a batch file:

  TW2002 TWNODE=%1 > ERR%1.LOG

Then view ERR.LOG or ERR?.LOG after the game ends to see what it reported.
It is important to include the node number in the log file when calling the
game from a batch file because if two sessions attempt to open the same log
file there will be a share violation.  This is a confusing situation as no
error will can be generated.

